metadata.name: Automata Monads #40
metadata.description:
“In the end, every system that follows definite rules can be thought of as a cellular automaton.”
Stephen Wolfram

Our thoughts and our universe consist of systems that may seem chaotic but fundamentally operate according to specific rules. Cellular automata are a model where these rules come to life in a simple yet profound way. Each cell evolves solely based on its neighboring cells, following a deterministic process. This evolutionary progression transforms an initially simple order into complex and mesmerizing patterns over time. Just like in nature, every small interaction is part of a grand transformation. The universe of cellular automata is a dynamic structure that follows rules yet remains full of surprises.  

This collection was created to explore the aesthetic and mathematical beauty of cellular automata. Each piece visualizes how a complex order emerges from simple rules. The interactions between colors, forms, and structures reveal the depth and power of the system's rules. Inspired by iconic collections such as "RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton," my goal with this project is to bring together the evolutionary beauty of fundamental rules in both natural and artificial systems and to open a window into the essence of these models through an interactive approach.

[R] Cam mode / Reset to start point
[W] Forward move
[S] Backward move
[A] Left move
[D] Right move
[Hold Shift] Fast move
[ESC] Disable pointer lock
———————————————————
[Q] Start and stop animation
[E] Fullscreen mode
[Z] Save image as a PNG
* Interactive mode works best on a new window.

metadata.name: Perlin Sun #27
metadata.description:
"Perlin Sun" by Marnix Keller consists of 52 pieces, one for each week of the year.

It has at it's centre, a sun consisting of two colours.  A base colour overlaid with another of Perlin noise.

There are 5 possible sun palettes:
"Strawberries and lime"
"Harvest gold"
"White heat"
"Blood orange"
"Margarita"

There are 6 possible sky palettes:
"Azure"
"Arctic twilight"
"Purple haze"
"Desert days"
"Mountain air"
"Skyfall"

There are 5 possible ground palettes:
"Green grass of home"
"Distant shores"
"Meadow mountain"
"Sandy lane"
"The north island"
            
There is the possibility of clouds and birds, but these are rare...

metadata.name: Skull Legion #1
metadata.description: In the ruins of an ancient city ravaged by great wars, warriors rise from the ashes—skeletal champions cursed by dark magic. Once noble heroes, they are now bound to serve the shadows of a black enchantment. Every step they take through the desolate city is a trial of strength and will, where traps of dark sorcery lurk at every turn.

metadata.name: Pumpkin Head #41
metadata.description: The creatures observed within the desolate cemetery of the city are commonly known as "pumpkin heads." According to local accounts, these entities are believed to be the most horrifying creatures in the entire city, instilling sheer terror in those who encounter them. It is rumored that the mere sound of their voices has the power to awaken the dormant zombies, causing them to rise from their graves once again.

metadata.name: fREEDOM PUNK #22
metadata.description:
Welcome to fREEDOM PUNK world.
This project is Image Composition Layers pngs.
Created with 128x128 px format.
There are 9 Layers in this project. (included transparent png files)
- Background > 130 different images
- Body > 12 different body colors.
- Eyes > 24 different eyes.
- Nose > 13 different noses.
- Mouth > 58 different mouths.
- Eyeglasses > 19 different eyeglasses. (chance of nothing is much higher)
- Hair > 133 different hair-styles and headwear.
- Cloth > 160 different clothes.
- Things (In front of the punk) > 60 different things. (chance of nothing is much higher)

So you can generate your unique fREEDOM PUNKs for sure, due to very high possibilities by the layers.

Enjoy and good luck!
